main event: Numerous moving unidentified targets were observed on both ground-radar and air-intercept radar in Southwest Bay, Labrador on September 5, 1961.
interesting points: Targets showed erratic and unpredictable movement at estimated speeds of 500-600 knots,Some targets remained stationary,The sighting lasted for approximately 3-5 minutes,The objects were visually observed by the KC-97 crew but were too fast for positive identification,The report emphasized the unusual and unidentified nature of the phenomena.
witness description: KC-97 crew visually observing the targets
